title: Eating Sweets
description: This randomly asks you how often you have eaten sweets in the last two hours. Eventually, it should give you a fair idea of how often you eat desserts. Tracking this might be good if you were planning on staying trim, or training for a half marathon in the fall or something :-) After a week, you should have a pretty good idea, and should stop the experiment.
informedConsentForm:
This is an experiment I created for myself. I decided to share it as an example for others to see. You may use it, but realize that the data will be visible to me. I have no interest in looking at anyone's data and I will not share it to anyone either for any purpose. I may make casual statements about aggregate statistics, but I will never reveal individual data items. 

If you want this to be really invisible to me and everyone else, just make a new version of the experiment for yourself.

There is no warranty of fitness, safety or anything else for the data gathered in this experiment. You are on your own.
creator: bobevans999@gmail.com

title: Happy Work Day
description:
This experiment randomly asks you how your work day is going. 

The theory is that over a long enough period of time, you will get a sense of your work experience and whether you should fix something, or bask in satisfaction.
informedConsentForm:
Once again, this is an alpha service, and we make no promises that this is good for anything, that the data will survive, or that it will be safe. 

That said, we are trying to make it safe and private. We will not share your data with anyone. We will not even look at the data other than in aggregate. 

If you want to, you can create an experiment like this for yourself and then it will not be shared with the creator of this experiment.

title: Japanese mojibake test
description:
This experiment attempts to show a question in Japanese to see if the text shows up without getting "garbled". The experiment definition was created on a PC, English Windows OS (7 Pro), Firefox browser, with Japanese text enabled using the control panel.

この実験は日本語の文字化け状況を診断するためのものです。
informedConsentForm:
This experiment has been set up for technical testing only and not as an instrument for testing psychological states. Please help us if you are able to understand Japanese. 

技術的な問題を診断するための実験であり、心理テストではありません。
creator: emimakinojp@gmail.com

title: Sit up straight log
description:
A willpower exercise from Roy Baumeister's book, WillPower.

Use this for two weeks. During that two weeks, every time you remember, remind yourself to sit up straight. Then record it here. It is self-report only. No signal.

They pre and post tested willpower by measuring time that you could squeeze a hand-grip spring.
informedConsentForm: Do not use this unless you are comfortable with your data disappearing. It is an alpha service. No warranties or guarantees whatsoever. It is not a medical application either so don't use it like that, OK?
creator: bobevans999@gmail.com

title: Time Flies
description:
This experiment is modeled after Conti's (2001) study of the connection between intrinsic motivation and the experience of time.
Notes:
75 undergrad students between 18-22 yrs old. 25 were paid $20.

Conti, R. Time flies: investigating the connection between intrinsic motivation and the experience of time. Journal of Personality 69:1, Feb 2001. pp.1-26.
informedConsentForm:
This independent experiment was created by Emi Makino, a doctoral student at CGU. Data collected will be de-identified and kept anonymous. Please send comments and feedback to emimakinojp@gmail.com.

Thank you for taking part!
creator: emimakinojp@gmail.com
